creator: Charles Homer Haskins
description:
LibriVox recording of The Normans in European History by Charles Homer Haskins.
Read in English by Pamela Nagami

Wherever their ships took them, the Normans (Northman) were ruthless conquerors but gifted governors. These eight lectures given in Boston in 1915 by the eminent Harvard medievalist, Charles Homer Haskins, chronicle the achievements of these descendants of the Vikings, whose genius for assimilation transformed them into French, English, and Sicilian citizens of well-run states. - Summary by Pamela Nagami

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audiobooks or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
